26/08/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Police arrested seven people in Pristina on Wednesday (August 25th) for allegedly misusing bank cards and stealing up to 150,000 euros. The group is suspected of copying bank cards, mainly those of US citizens working in Kosovo. "They were hackers and stole the data from the internet and then copied bank cards," Kosovo Police spokesperson Baki Kelani explained. Police seized guns, laptops and other equipment that the group allegedly used to commit their crimes. (Express, Koha Ditore, Zeri, Kosova Sot - 26/08/10)
